entry.title: Festuca muelleri
entry.content: Tall, wide, thick, robust grass. One plant on the dirt roadside heading down from the Horn.

entry.title: Acacia alpina
entry.content: Common along the short dirt road leading to The Horn.

entry.title: Tasmannia xerophila subsp. xerophila
entry.content: One flower visible with 2 petals. Growing in rocks in open herb-field. Altitude ~1470m.

entry.title: Hovea montana
entry.content: Nearly all plants had finished flowering.

entry.title: Celmisia pugioniformis
entry.content: Slender leaves. Seemed to be finishing flowering (flowers scruffy looking) whereas the broad-leaved C. tomentella growing with it hadn't started flowering yet.

entry.title: Grevillea alpivaga
entry.content: To 1m tall and spreading. Midrib on underside of leaf is visible which suggests it is G. alpivaga, not G. australis. Flowering with Kunzea parvifolia.

entry.title: Graphium macleayanus moggana, Westringia senifolia
entry.content: Host plant for Swallowtail at this location would probably be that described in observation 7933 (Tasmannia xerophila subsp. xerophila).
